File: While mop-up operations continue in Cape Town, preparations are under way for more rain on Sunday. CAPE TOWN - More rain is expected to hit Cape Town on Sunday. On Friday, heavy rain caused localised flooding. READ: Heavy rains hit Cape Town Roads in formal and informal areas were submerged and some areas were left without power. Blocked drains caused by waste being dumped in it, was a major contributing factor to the flooding.
"Citywide we were inundated with calls about flooding taking place," said the City of Cape Town's Samuel Freeman. READ: Cape Town disaster management on standby after flooding With more rain forecast for Sunday, city officials are on standby.
"Every department within the City of Cape Town has its own contingency plans, so departments have crews on standby." said Freeman.